&gt;&gt;&gt; 1.Now that I can remember my login credentials. But can I remove the
&gt;&gt;&gt; login page and directly go into the heritrix mainpage?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; If you are visiting from the same browser without having quit and
&gt;&gt; relaunched the browser, you won&#39;t be prompted again. In most browsers,
&gt;&gt; even with a quit and relaunch, the values can be saved so you won&#39;t have
&gt;&gt; to re-type.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Why do you need to eliminate even that step? (Is there something else
&gt;&gt; you&#39;re trying to achieve?)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; You should also review this page about why it is important to limit
&gt;&gt; access to the administrative interface:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Security+Considerations
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; 2.Thanks for the depthe level setting advice ! It works!!!! and I am
&gt;&gt;&gt; gald abt it! Thanks!
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; 3. I still don&#39;t understand how to download more than a website at
&gt;&gt;&gt; the same time. Is it I just type in all the url addresses in the
&gt;&gt;&gt; seeds textbox, line by line then add in once again all the url
&gt;&gt;&gt; addresss in the http-header-user agent text box by adding &quot;+&quot; sign.
&gt;&gt;&gt; For example: seeds text box: http://www.abc.com http://www.def.com
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; http-header-user agent text box: Mozilla/5.0 (compatible;
&gt;&gt;&gt; heritrix/1.14.3 +http://www.abc.com +http://www.def.com)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; You should not be putting the URLs of the sites you&#39;re crawling into the
&gt;&gt; &#39;http-user-agent&#39; value!
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The HTTP &#39;User-Agent&#39; header is to identify *you* to sites, allowing
&gt;&gt; them to contact you if anything goes wrong. The URL should be an URL
&gt;&gt; that describes your purpose in crawling and includes contact information
&gt;&gt; such as an email address or phone number.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; This is covered in the H1 User Manual, among other places:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/config.html#httpheaders
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; 4.Why is it after we key in the url in the seed box then we need to
&gt;&gt;&gt; re-keyin the url once agin into the http-header-user agent text box
&gt;&gt;&gt; and somemore we need to provide our email add in the &quot;from&quot; texbox?
&gt;&gt;&gt; It seems like doing double work. Can we simplify this? Is there any
